/-!
# Dirichlet-kernel exact quadrature (self-contained)

This module builds the exact "reproducing" quadrature machinery used to bridge a continuous
integral against a continuous window and a discrete windowed grid sum.

The key object is the (real) Dirichlet kernel `dirichletKernel M s = 1 + 2 ∑_{k=1}^M cos(2π k s)`.
It reproduces the values of any real trigonometric polynomial of degree `≤ M` at a point `a`
through integration over the unit interval:
`∫ t, cos(2π m t) · dirichletKernel M (t - a) dt = cos(2π m a)` whenever `|m| ≤ M`.

Extending this by the product-to-sum expansion yields the exact reproducing identity for a product
of cosines with integer frequencies whose absolute values sum to at most `M`, and, summing the
kernel over a grid, the exact windowed quadrature identity `prod_cos_reproWindow`.

Everything here is stated over the unit interval `unitInterval` with the `volume` measure, so that
it transfers verbatim to `X₀ := I` and `μ₀ := volume` used elsewhere in the project.
-/

